"On draft at the Hourglass Brewery. Pitch black body with hardly any head. I can pick out the chilies in the aroma along with a lot more coffee than expected. Chocolate is also present. The taste is coffee forward along with a complex blend of sweet milk chocolate, dark chocolate, and vanilla. There is a vegetable taste from the peppers that I do not care for. I get medium heat from the chilies and very minimal alcohol presence for the ABV. The mouth feel is very smooth, but I would prefer a little more body. This is a very well crafted beer and I would like to have it again; but I don't care for the vegetable taste."
