"Picked this up in a trade with Cisco!  Thick, pitch black pour with a nice two finger caramel-colored head that fades quickly with minimal lacing.  The nose is absolutely huge and complex, dominated by big roasty coffee and surprisingly strong chili notes.  Hints of dark chocolate, cocoa, vanilla, espresso, and leather.  The taste mirrors the nose with all the featured elements sharing the spotlight equally.  Huge roasty coffee with fudgy dark chocolate, cocoa, espresso, chilies, and vanilla.  The mouthfeel is thick, creamy, and mouth-coating with incredible balance and huge drinkability with subtle chili heat on the finish.  Overall, this beer delivers in every way. All the advertised elements were bold, yet equally represented with over the top drinkability.  Right up there with Abraxas.  Highly recommended!"
""
