"This is by far Okla's best beer to date. The coffee flavor is apparent up front but not overpowering. Then the vanilla takes over to smooth it out , ending with a very slight spice (which is not spicy, but you can tell it was aged with chili peppers). I couldn't believe how well they hid 14% abv. This is one of the most impressive beers I've ever had. The only down side to this beer is the fact that it's a one time brew."
""
"Overall - This is an extremely solid stout, and is the best PAA beer I've had to date (which is saying a lot). It's incredibly smooth and flavorful, and really hides its 14% ABV. With so much going on, beers like this risk being unbalanced. However, here, the flavors all complement one another and all are expressed adequately. I can't wait to see how this ages."
